## Step 3 — Add Real Images and Short Videos

Performance Max uses image and video assets across YouTube, Display, Discover, and more.[web:93][web:99] If you don’t upload strong ones:

- Google will **autogenerate video** from whatever’s on your site.[web:93]
- It will pull random images, including weak stock art, to build creatives.[web:93][web:96]

That can hurt click-through rate and brand perception, even if you never meant to run those exact creatives.

**What to do:**

- Add **real photos** on key pages:
  - your team,
  - your work / product,
  - real customers / finished jobs.
- Shoot **simple 15–30 second videos** (phone is fine) that:
  - show the product/service in action,
  - state who you help and how,
  - include a simple call to action.

Upload those into Google Ads and ensure those same assets are present on your landing pages so AI has good, on-brand material.[web:93][web:99]

This also helps with **multimodal search**, where Google can surface video directly in AI answers and SERPs.[web:99]

