## Step 4 — Fix Your Product Feed (If You Sell Online)

For e‑commerce, Performance Max heavily depends on your **Google Merchant Center product feed**.[web:93][web:99] That feed tells Google what each product is and when to show it.

Most brands under-fill fields, leaving AI blind on details.

**Key feed fields that matter:**

- product title and description,
- brand,
- color, size, material,
- price and availability,
- GTIN/MPN where relevant.[web:93][web:97][web:100]

**Why it matters:**

- Richer product data lets AI match long-tail queries more accurately (“blue waterproof hiking jacket size M”) and shows more relevant items.[web:93][web:97]
- Detailed feeds are tied to better ad quality and higher CTR through richer snippets and shopping placements.[web:97][web:100]

**Fix:**

- Audit your feed and aim to fill **every relevant field** for top-selling products.
- Make titles and descriptions human-readable and keyword-rich but not spammy.

